## Discovery Dashboard

When the TPM wants to consolidate after one or more meetings, produce a **Discovery Dashboard** as a persistent Cowork artifact using `mcp__cowork__create_artifact`. This is what the TPM keeps coming back to as discovery progresses, and uses as the foundation for writing the PRD.

### How to create it

Call `mcp__cowork__create_artifact` with:
- `name`: "Discovery Dashboard — [Project Name]"
- `description`: "Live discovery summary for [Project Name] — what we know, open decisions and risks, and PRD readiness"
- `mcp_tools`: [] (no live connector data needed — content is populated from meeting notes)

### Dashboard structure (HTML)

Build the artifact as a single-page HTML dashboard with these sections:

**1. Header** — project name, TPM name, date, status badge (In Progress / Ready for PRD)

**2. Metric strip** — four summary cards: items captured, decisions needed, risks flagged, blockers. Use amber text for decisions/risks, red for blockers.

**3. Information cards (2×2 grid)**
- Business case — what problem, for whom, cost of inaction, timeline forcing function
- Success criteria — specific measurable targets, listed as pills
- Scope — three sub-sections: In / Out / Nice to have
- Technical approach — recommended approach, phasing, effort estimate

**4. Risk & Decision Register table** — columns: Item, Type, Owner, Status, Impact. Colour-code type badges:
  - Blocker = danger (red)
  - Decision needed = warning (amber)
  - Risk = info (blue)
  - Follow-up = secondary (grey)

**5. Ready for PRD? verdict** — the most important section. Show a clear badge (Not yet / Almost / Ready). List each outstanding blocker or decision as a named action item with a specific owner. Be direct — name exactly what's standing between the TPM and writing the PRD. Include a "Mark items resolved ↗" button using `sendPrompt`.

### Styling rules

Use CSS variables throughout (`var(--color-background-primary)`, `var(--color-text-primary)`, etc.) so the dashboard works in both light and dark mode. Cards use `border: 0.5px solid var(--color-border-tertiary)` and `border-radius: var(--border-radius-lg)`. The "Ready for PRD?" section uses a `1.5px` border in the appropriate semantic colour (warning if not ready, success if ready). All text in sentence case, font-weight 400 or 500 only.

### Updating the dashboard

When the TPM resolves items or adds new meeting notes, use `mcp__cowork__update_artifact` to refresh the dashboard in place — same artifact, updated content. Don't create a new one each time.

